    • dev - Tables supporting compilation of programs
      • dev.arch - System architecture

      • dev.htmlentity - Known HTML entity strings & codes
      • dev.include - A site where one file includes another
      • dev.license - Source code license
      • dev.linelim -

      • dev.msgfile - File in repo containing messages that should be normalized during CI
      • dev.noindent - Indicates that a file should not be automatically indented
      • dev.opt_type - Type of option (used in tool_opt)
      • dev.package - OpenACR package

      • dev.pkgkey - Keys belonging to the OpenACR package
      • dev.readme - File containing documentation

      • dev.scriptfile - Known script file
      • dev.srcfile - Source file or header (key is pathname)

    • dmmeta - Tables holding metadata (data model meta)
      • dmmeta.anonfld - Omit field name where possible (command line, enums, constants)
      • dmmeta.argvtype - Customize parsing of command lines (rarely used)
      • dmmeta.basepool - Specify pool to be used for allocating elements of a type
      • dmmeta.bitfld - Specify offset/width of a bitfield within another field
      • dmmeta.cafter - Control amc processing order for unrelated types (used in rare situations)
      • dmmeta.cascdel - Request cascading delete of referenced rows
      • dmmeta.ccmp - Generate hash function
      • dmmeta.cdflt - Specify default value for single-value types that lack fields
      • dmmeta.cextern - Externally defined ctype (a struct from system header, or from a c++ library)
      • dmmeta.cfast - FAST properties for ctype
      • dmmeta.cfmt - Specify options for printing/reading ctypes into multiple formats
      • dmmeta.cget - Generate state functions for these ctypes
      • dmmeta.charset - Generate functions to determine if a character is a member of a set
      • dmmeta.chash - Generate hash function
      • dmmeta.cppfunc - Value of field provided by this expression
      • dmmeta.cppkeyword - Built-in C++ keyword
      • dmmeta.cpptype - Specify whether a ctype can be passed by value, and other c++ options
      • dmmeta.csize - Specify size/alignment for built-in C++ types
      • dmmeta.cstr - Specify that type behaves like a string
      • dmmeta.ctype - Struct
      • dmmeta.ctypelen - Size of Ctype
      • dmmeta.dispatch - Generate code for a multi-way branch
      • dmmeta.dispatch_msg - Add message to a dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispctx - Use context with dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispfilter - Generate filter function on dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispsig - Cryptographic signature of all dispatches
      • dmmeta.dispsigcheck - Check signature of input data against executable’s version
      • dmmeta.disptrace - Generate trace fields (cycles, counts) for all dispatch branches
      • dmmeta.falias - Alias field
      • dmmeta.fastenc -
      • dmmeta.fastinstr -
      • dmmeta.fastop -
      • dmmeta.fbase - Customize imported Base fields
      • dmmeta.fbigend - Annotate field as having big-endian storage
      • dmmeta.fbitset - Generate bitset functions over integer field or array
      • dmmeta.fbuf - Buffer for reading/writing messages, works with Iohook
      • dmmeta.fbufdir - Buffer direction (in,out)
      • dmmeta.fbuftype - Buffer type
      • dmmeta.fcast - Generate implicit conversion from field to c++ expression
      • dmmeta.fcleanup - Request user-implemented function to be called at Uninit time for a field
      • dmmeta.fcmap - Bidirectional mapping between fconst values
      • dmmeta.fcmdline - Annotate field that holds process command line
      • dmmeta.fcmp - Request versionsort or case-insensitive sort for field
      • dmmeta.fcompact - Request compaction upon removal from index
      • dmmeta.fconst - Specify enum value (integer + string constant) for a field
      • dmmeta.fcurs - Request generation of custom cursor
      • dmmeta.fdec - Specify that field has an implied # of decimal places and specify formatting options
      • dmmeta.fdelay - Control elapsed time between execution of a step
      • dmmeta.ffast - FAST properties for field
      • dmmeta.fflag - Options for command-line flags
      • dmmeta.field - Specify field of a struct
      • dmmeta.findrem - Request generation of FindRemove function
      • dmmeta.finput - Describe input table of a program
      • dmmeta.fldoffset - Assert field offset - will result in compile-time error if violated
      • dmmeta.floadtuples - Request that process automatically load any input tables on startup
      • dmmeta.fnoremove - Omit any functions for removing elements from table; Table is append-only
      • dmmeta.foutput - Generate function to save index/table back to disk
      • dmmeta.fprefix - Mapping between field prefix and Reftype
      • dmmeta.fregx - Specify options for command-line regx field
      • dmmeta.fsort - Generate custom sort function for array field
      • dmmeta.fstep - Generate a main loop step to be executed whenever a field is non-empty
      • dmmeta.ftrace - Generate cycle/step counting fields for a step
      • dmmeta.ftuple -
      • dmmeta.func -
      • dmmeta.funique - This field must be unique in the table. Not needed for primary key
      • dmmeta.fuserinit - Add user-defined initialization function for field (see fcleanup)
      • dmmeta.fwddecl - Request forward declaration of a field
      • dmmeta.gconst - Import ssim table columns as fconst for a field
      • dmmeta.gstatic - Load entries for this table at startup time
      • dmmeta.gsymbol - Create C++ symbols from entries in ssim table
      • dmmeta.hashtype - Hash function type
      • dmmeta.hook - Required on Hook fields
      • dmmeta.inlary - Generate inline array of fixed or variable length (all entries fit within parent struct)
      • dmmeta.lenfld - Specify which gives length of varlen portion in bytes
      • dmmeta.listtype - Specify structure of linked list based on field prefix
      • dmmeta.llist - Options for Llist field
      • dmmeta.logcat - Log category
      • dmmeta.main - Generate Main function for namespace
      • dmmeta.msgtype - Specify message type for each eligible message, controls dispatch
      • dmmeta.nocascdel - Remove cascade delete for this index
      • dmmeta.nossimfile - Indicates that ssimfile does not exist for this ssimdb ctype
      • dmmeta.noxref - Explicitly specify that no x-ref exists between tables (don’t use unless forced)
      • dmmeta.ns - Namespace (for in-memory database, protocol, etc)
      • dmmeta.nscpp - Generate C++ code for this namespace
      • dmmeta.nsdb - Annotate ssimdb namespaces
      • dmmeta.nsfast - Whether namespace is FAST
      • dmmeta.nsinclude - Explicitly specify a C++ include file for namespace
      • dmmeta.nsjs - Generate JavaScript code for this namespace
      • dmmeta.nsproto - Annotate protocol namespace (collection of types, no state)
      • dmmeta.nstype - Namespace type
      • dmmeta.nsversion - Namespace version
      • dmmeta.nsx - Control code-generation and exception handling options for process/library
      • dmmeta.numstr - Add functions to read numbers out of a string field
      • dmmeta.pack - Request byte-packing of structure fields
      • dmmeta.pmaskfld - Specify which field holds presence mask bits (one for each field in struct)
      • dmmeta.pmaskfld_member - Explicit field-to-pmask association
      • dmmeta.pnew - Generate custom constructor (placement new), for use with binary protocols
      • dmmeta.pnewtype - Type of fbuf
      • dmmeta.printfmt - Print format
      • dmmeta.ptrary - Required for fields with reftype:Ptrary
      • dmmeta.reftype - Field type constructor (e.g. reference type)
      • dmmeta.rowid - Initialize field to row id of element
      • dmmeta.smallstr - Generated fixed-length padded or length-delimited string field
      • dmmeta.sortfld - Specify what field an index (Bheap,Atree) is sorted on
      • dmmeta.sorttype - Sort type
      • dmmeta.sqltype - Mapping of ctype -> SQL expression
      • dmmeta.ssimfile - File with ssim tuples
      • dmmeta.ssimreq - Extended constraints for ssim records
      • dmmeta.ssimsort - Define sort order for ssimfile
      • dmmeta.ssimvolatile - Types based on ssim files marked this way cannot be cross-referenced
      • dmmeta.steptype - Type of scheduler step
      • dmmeta.strfmt - Cfmt conversion type (misnomer, not necessarily a string)
      • dmmeta.strtype - Type of small string
      • dmmeta.substr - Specify that the field value is computed from a substring of another field
      • dmmeta.svtype - Table for determining ctype from separated value file
      • dmmeta.tary - Indirect linear dynamically alocated array (used for strings, arrays of data, etc)
      • dmmeta.thash - Hash index, required for fields with reftype Thash
      • dmmeta.tracefld - Trace fields
      • dmmeta.tracerec - Trace record
      • dmmeta.typefld - Specifies which field of a message carries the type
      • dmmeta.usertracefld - Add custom user trace fields to process’s trace struct
      • dmmeta.xref - Specify how to cross-reference (i.e. project, or group-by) one record with another

  599// --- dmmeta.Anonfld..ReadFieldMaybe
  600bool dmmeta::Anonfld_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Anonfld& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
  601    bool retval = true;
  602    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
  603    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
  604    switch(field_id) {
  605        case dmmeta_FieldId_field: {
  606            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.field, strval);
  607            break;
  608        }
  609        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
  610            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
  611            break;
  612        }
  613        default: break;
  614    }
  615    if (!retval) {
  616        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
  617    }
  618    return retval;
  619}
  620
  621// --- dmmeta.Anonfld..ReadStrptrMaybe
  622// Read fields of dmmeta::Anonfld from an ascii string.
  623// The format of the string is an ssim Tuple
  624bool dmmeta::Anonfld_ReadStrptrMaybe(dmmeta::Anonfld &parent, algo::strptr in_str) {
  625    bool retval = true;
  626    retval = algo::StripTypeTag(in_str, "dmmeta.anonfld") || algo::StripTypeTag(in_str, "dmmeta.Anonfld");
  627    ind_beg(algo::Attr_curs, attr, in_str) {
  628        retval = retval && Anonfld_ReadFieldMaybe(parent, attr.name, attr.value);
  629    }ind_end;
  630    return retval;
  631}

  633// --- dmmeta.Anonfld..Print
  634// print string representation of ROW to string STR
  635// cfmt:dmmeta.Anonfld.String  printfmt:Tuple
  636void dmmeta::Anonfld_Print(dmmeta::Anonfld& row, algo::cstring& str) {
  637    algo::tempstr temp;
  638    str << "dmmeta.anonfld";
  639
  640    algo::Smallstr100_Print(row.field, temp);
  641    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"field", temp);
  642
  643    algo::Comment_Print(row.comment, temp);
  644    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"comment", temp);
  645}

  762// --- dmmeta.Bitfld..ReadFieldMaybe
  763bool dmmeta::Bitfld_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Bitfld& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
  764    bool retval = true;
  765    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
  766    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
  767    switch(field_id) {
  768        case dmmeta_FieldId_field: {
  769            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.field, strval);
  770            break;
  771        }
  772        case dmmeta_FieldId_name: {
  773            retval = false;
  774            break;
  775        }
  776        case dmmeta_FieldId_offset: {
  777            retval = i32_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.offset, strval);
  778            break;
  779        }
  780        case dmmeta_FieldId_width: {
  781            retval = i32_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.width, strval);
  782            break;
  783        }
  784        case dmmeta_FieldId_srcfield: {
  785            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.srcfield, strval);
  786            break;
  787        }
  788        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
  789            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
  790            break;
  791        }
  792        default: break;
  793    }
  794    if (!retval) {
  795        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
  796    }
  797    return retval;
  798}

  812// --- dmmeta.Bitfld..Print
  813// print string representation of ROW to string STR
  814// cfmt:dmmeta.Bitfld.String  printfmt:Tuple
  815void dmmeta::Bitfld_Print(dmmeta::Bitfld& row, algo::cstring& str) {
  816    algo::tempstr temp;
  817    str << "dmmeta.bitfld";
  818
  819    algo::Smallstr100_Print(row.field, temp);
  820    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"field", temp);
  821
  822    i32_Print(row.offset, temp);
  823    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"offset", temp);
  824
  825    i32_Print(row.width, temp);
  826    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"width", temp);
  827
  828    algo::Smallstr100_Print(row.srcfield, temp);
  829    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"srcfield", temp);
  830
  831    algo::Comment_Print(row.comment, temp);
  832    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"comment", temp);
  833}

 1016// --- dmmeta.Ccmp..ReadFieldMaybe
 1017bool dmmeta::Ccmp_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Ccmp& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
 1018    bool retval = true;
 1019    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
 1020    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
 1021    switch(field_id) {
 1022        case dmmeta_FieldId_ctype: {
 1023            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.ctype, strval);
 1024            break;
 1025        }
 1026        case dmmeta_FieldId_extrn: {
 1027            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.extrn, strval);
 1028            break;
 1029        }
 1030        case dmmeta_FieldId_genop: {
 1031            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.genop, strval);
 1032            break;
 1033        }
 1034        case dmmeta_FieldId_order: {
 1035            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.order, strval);
 1036            break;
 1037        }
 1038        case dmmeta_FieldId_minmax: {
 1039            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.minmax, strval);
 1040            break;
 1041        }
 1042        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
 1043            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
 1044            break;
 1045        }
 1046        default: break;
 1047    }
 1048    if (!retval) {
 1049        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 1050    }

 1328// --- dmmeta.Cfmt..ReadFieldMaybe
 1329bool dmmeta::Cfmt_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Cfmt& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
 1330    bool retval = true;
 1331    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
 1332    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
 1333    switch(field_id) {
 1334        case dmmeta_FieldId_cfmt: {
 1335            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.cfmt, strval);
 1336            break;
 1337        }
 1338        case dmmeta_FieldId_ctype: {
 1339            retval = false;
 1340            break;
 1341        }
 1342        case dmmeta_FieldId_strfmt: {
 1343            retval = false;
 1344            break;
 1345        }
 1346        case dmmeta_FieldId_printfmt: {
 1347            retval = algo::Smallstr50_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.printfmt, strval);
 1348            break;
 1349        }
 1350        case dmmeta_FieldId_read: {
 1351            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.read, strval);
 1352            break;
 1353        }
 1354        case dmmeta_FieldId_print: {
 1355            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.print, strval);
 1356            break;
 1357        }
 1358        case dmmeta_FieldId_sep: {
 1359            retval = algo::Smallstr20_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.sep, strval);
 1360            break;
 1361        }
 1362        case dmmeta_FieldId_genop: {
 1363            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.genop, strval);
 1364            break;
 1365        }
 1366        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
 1367            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
 1368            break;
 1369        }
 1370        default: break;
 1371    }
 1372    if (!retval) {
 1373        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 1374    }
 1375    return retval;
 1376}

 2099            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
 2100            break;

 2204        case dmmeta_FieldId_dispatch: {
 2205            retval = false;
 2206            break;
 2207        }
 2208        case dmmeta_FieldId_ctype: {
 2209            retval = false;
 2210            break;
 2211        }
 2212        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
 2213            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
 2214            break;
 2215        }
 2216        default: break;
 2217    }
 2218    if (!retval) {
 2219        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 2220    }
 2221    return retval;
 2222}

 2651// --- dmmeta.FastencCase.fastenc.ToCstr
 2652// Convert numeric value of field to one of predefined string constants.
 2653// If string is found, return a static C string. Otherwise, return NULL.
 2654const char* dmmeta::fastenc_ToCstr(const dmmeta::FastencCase& parent) {
 2655    const char *ret = NULL;
 2656    switch(fastenc_GetEnum(parent)) {
 2657        case dmmeta_FastencCase_byteVector : ret = "byteVector";  break;
 2658        case dmmeta_FastencCase_group      : ret = "group";  break;
 2659        case dmmeta_FastencCase_scaled     : ret = "scaled";  break;
 2660        case dmmeta_FastencCase_sequence   : ret = "sequence";  break;
 2661        case dmmeta_FastencCase_signed     : ret = "signed";  break;
 2662        case dmmeta_FastencCase_string     : ret = "string";  break;
 2663        case dmmeta_FastencCase_template   : ret = "template";  break;
 2664        case dmmeta_FastencCase_type       : ret = "type";  break;
 2665        case dmmeta_FastencCase_unsigned   : ret = "unsigned";  break;
 2666    }
 2667    return ret;
 2668}
 2669
 2670// --- dmmeta.FastencCase.fastenc.Print
 2671// Convert fastenc to a string. First, attempt conversion to a known string.
 2672// If no string matches, print fastenc as a numeric value.
 2673void dmmeta::fastenc_Print(const dmmeta::FastencCase& parent, algo::cstring &lhs) {
 2674    const char *strval = fastenc_ToCstr(parent);
 2675    if (strval) {
 2676        lhs << strval;
 2677    } else {
 2678        lhs << parent.fastenc;
 2679    }
 2680}
 2681
 2682// --- dmmeta.FastencCase.fastenc.SetStrptrMaybe
 2683// Convert string to field.
 2684// If the string is invalid, do not modify field and return false.
 2685// In case of success, return true
 2686bool dmmeta::fastenc_SetStrptrMaybe(dmmeta::FastencCase& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
 2687    bool ret = false;
 2688    switch (elems_N(rhs)) {
 2689        case 4: {
 2690            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))) {
 2691                case LE_STR4('t','y','p','e'): {
 2692                    fastenc_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastencCase_type); ret = true; break;
 2693                }
 2694            }
 2695            break;
 2696        }
 2697        case 5: {
 2698            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(rhs[4])<<32)) {
 2699                case LE_STR5('g','r','o','u','p'): {
 2700                    fastenc_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastencCase_group); ret = true; break;
 2701                }
 2702            }
 2703            break;
 2704        }
 2705        case 6: {
 2706            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(algo::ReadLE16(rhs.elems+4))<<32)) {
 2707                case LE_STR6('s','c','a','l','e','d'): {
 2708                    fastenc_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastencCase_scaled); ret = true; break;
 2709                }
 2710                case LE_STR6('s','i','g','n','e','d'): {
 2711                    fastenc_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastencCase_signed); ret = true; break;
 2712                }
 2713                case LE_STR6('s','t','r','i','n','g'): {
 2714                    fastenc_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastencCase_string); ret = true; break;
 2715                }
 2716            }
 2717            break;
 2718        }
 2719        case 8: {
 2720            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
 2721                case LE_STR8('s','e','q','u','e','n','c','e'): {
 2722                    fastenc_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastencCase_sequence); ret = true; break;
 2723                }
 2724                case LE_STR8('t','e','m','p','l','a','t','e'): {
 2725                    fastenc_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastencCase_template); ret = true; break;
 2726                }
 2727                case LE_STR8('u','n','s','i','g','n','e','d'): {
 2728                    fastenc_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastencCase_unsigned); ret = true; break;
 2729                }
 2730            }
 2731            break;
 2732        }
 2733        case 10: {
 2734            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
 2735                case LE_STR8('b','y','t','e','V','e','c','t'): {
 2736                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"or",2)==0) { fastenc_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastencCase_byteVector); ret = true; break; }
 2737                    break;
 2738                }
 2739            }
 2740            break;
 2741        }
 2742    }
 2743    return ret;
 2744}
 2745
 2746// --- dmmeta.FastencCase.fastenc.SetStrptr
 2747// Convert string to field.
 2748// If the string is invalid, set numeric value to DFLT

 2801// --- dmmeta.FastinstrCase.fastinstr.ToCstr
 2802// Convert numeric value of field to one of predefined string constants.
 2803// If string is found, return a static C string. Otherwise, return NULL.
 2804const char* dmmeta::fastinstr_ToCstr(const dmmeta::FastinstrCase& parent) {
 2805    const char *ret = NULL;
 2806    switch(fastinstr_GetEnum(parent)) {
 2807        case dmmeta_FastinstrCase_field    : ret = "field";  break;
 2808        case dmmeta_FastinstrCase_length   : ret = "length";  break;
 2809        case dmmeta_FastinstrCase_mantissa : ret = "mantissa";  break;
 2810    }
 2811    return ret;
 2812}

 2814// --- dmmeta.FastinstrCase.fastinstr.Print
 2815// Convert fastinstr to a string. First, attempt conversion to a known string.
 2816// If no string matches, print fastinstr as a numeric value.
 2817void dmmeta::fastinstr_Print(const dmmeta::FastinstrCase& parent, algo::cstring &lhs) {
 2818    const char *strval = fastinstr_ToCstr(parent);
 2819    if (strval) {
 2820        lhs << strval;
 2821    } else {
 2822        lhs << parent.fastinstr;
 2823    }
 2824}

 2826// --- dmmeta.FastinstrCase.fastinstr.SetStrptrMaybe
 2827// Convert string to field.
 2828// If the string is invalid, do not modify field and return false.
 2829// In case of success, return true
 2830bool dmmeta::fastinstr_SetStrptrMaybe(dmmeta::FastinstrCase& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
 2831    bool ret = false;
 2832    switch (elems_N(rhs)) {
 2833        case 5: {
 2834            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(rhs[4])<<32)) {
 2835                case LE_STR5('f','i','e','l','d'): {
 2836                    fastinstr_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastinstrCase_field); ret = true; break;
 2837                }
 2838            }
 2839            break;
 2840        }
 2841        case 6: {
 2842            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(algo::ReadLE16(rhs.elems+4))<<32)) {
 2843                case LE_STR6('l','e','n','g','t','h'): {
 2844                    fastinstr_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastinstrCase_length); ret = true; break;
 2845                }
 2846            }
 2847            break;
 2848        }
 2849        case 8: {
 2850            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
 2851                case LE_STR8('m','a','n','t','i','s','s','a'): {
 2852                    fastinstr_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastinstrCase_mantissa); ret = true; break;
 2853                }
 2854            }
 2855            break;
 2856        }
 2857    }
 2858    return ret;
 2859}

 2916// --- dmmeta.FastopCase.fastop.ToCstr
 2917// Convert numeric value of field to one of predefined string constants.
 2918// If string is found, return a static C string. Otherwise, return NULL.
 2919const char* dmmeta::fastop_ToCstr(const dmmeta::FastopCase& parent) {
 2920    const char *ret = NULL;
 2921    switch(fastop_GetEnum(parent)) {
 2922        case dmmeta_FastopCase_constant    : ret = "constant";  break;
 2923        case dmmeta_FastopCase_copy        : ret = "copy";  break;
 2924        case dmmeta_FastopCase_default     : ret = "default";  break;
 2925        case dmmeta_FastopCase_delta       : ret = "delta";  break;
 2926        case dmmeta_FastopCase_increment   : ret = "increment";  break;
 2927        case dmmeta_FastopCase_none        : ret = "none";  break;
 2928        case dmmeta_FastopCase_tail        : ret = "tail";  break;
 2929    }
 2930    return ret;
 2931}

 2945// --- dmmeta.FastopCase.fastop.SetStrptrMaybe
 2946// Convert string to field.
 2947// If the string is invalid, do not modify field and return false.
 2948// In case of success, return true
 2949bool dmmeta::fastop_SetStrptrMaybe(dmmeta::FastopCase& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
 2950    bool ret = false;
 2951    switch (elems_N(rhs)) {
 2952        case 4: {
 2953            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))) {
 2954                case LE_STR4('c','o','p','y'): {
 2955                    fastop_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastopCase_copy); ret = true; break;
 2956                }
 2957                case LE_STR4('n','o','n','e'): {
 2958                    fastop_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastopCase_none); ret = true; break;
 2959                }
 2960                case LE_STR4('t','a','i','l'): {
 2961                    fastop_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastopCase_tail); ret = true; break;
 2962                }
 2963            }
 2964            break;
 2965        }
 2966        case 5: {
 2967            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(rhs[4])<<32)) {
 2968                case LE_STR5('d','e','l','t','a'): {
 2969                    fastop_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastopCase_delta); ret = true; break;
 2970                }
 2971            }
 2972            break;
 2973        }
 2974        case 7: {
 2975            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(algo::ReadLE16(rhs.elems+4))<<32)|(u64(rhs[6])<<48)) {
 2976                case LE_STR7('d','e','f','a','u','l','t'): {
 2977                    fastop_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastopCase_default); ret = true; break;
 2978                }
 2979            }
 2980            break;
 2981        }
 2982        case 8: {
 2983            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
 2984                case LE_STR8('c','o','n','s','t','a','n','t'): {
 2985                    fastop_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastopCase_constant); ret = true; break;
 2986                }
 2987            }
 2988            break;
 2989        }
 2990        case 9: {
 2991            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
 2992                case LE_STR8('i','n','c','r','e','m','e','n'): {
 2993                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"t",1)==0) { fastop_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FastopCase_increment); ret = true; break; }
 2994                    break;
 2995                }
 2996            }
 2997            break;
 2998        }
 2999    }
 3000    return ret;
 3001}

 3007    if (!fastop_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs)) fastop_SetEnum(parent,dflt);
 3008}

 3556            retval = false;

 3828// --- dmmeta.Fconst..ReadFieldMaybe
 3829bool dmmeta::Fconst_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Fconst& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
 3830    bool retval = true;
 3831    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
 3832    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);

 3834        case dmmeta_FieldId_fconst: {

 3836            break;
 3837        }
 3838        case dmmeta_FieldId_field: {
 3839            retval = false;
 3840            break;
 3841        }
 3842        case dmmeta_FieldId_value: {
 3843            retval = algo::CppExpr_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.value, strval);
 3844            break;
 3845        }
 3846        case dmmeta_FieldId_name: {
 3847            retval = false;
 3848            break;
 3849        }
 3850        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
 3851            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);

 4430        retval = retval && Field_ReadFieldMaybe(parent, attr.name, attr.value);
 4431    }ind_end;
 4432    return retval;
 4433}
 4434
 4435// --- dmmeta.Field..Print
 4436// print string representation of ROW to string STR
 4437// cfmt:dmmeta.Field.String  printfmt:Tuple
 4438void dmmeta::Field_Print(dmmeta::Field& row, algo::cstring& str) {
 4439    algo::tempstr temp;
 4440    str << "dmmeta.field";
 4441
 4442    algo::Smallstr100_Print(row.field, temp);
 4443    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"field", temp);
 4444
 4445    algo::Smallstr100_Print(row.arg, temp);
 4446    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"arg", temp);
 4447
 4448    algo::Smallstr50_Print(row.reftype, temp);
 4449    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"reftype", temp);
 4450
 4451    algo::CppExpr_Print(row.dflt, temp);
 4452    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"dflt", temp);
 4453
 4454    algo::Comment_Print(row.comment, temp);
 4455    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"comment", temp);
 4456}

 4652// --- dmmeta.FieldId.value.Print
 4653// Convert value to a string. First, attempt conversion to a known string.
 4654// If no string matches, print value as a numeric value.
 4655void dmmeta::value_Print(const dmmeta::FieldId& parent, algo::cstring &lhs) {
 4656    const char *strval = value_ToCstr(parent);
 4657    if (strval) {
 4658        lhs << strval;
 4659    } else {
 4660        lhs << parent.value;
 4661    }
 4662}

 4664// --- dmmeta.FieldId.value.SetStrptrMaybe
 4665// Convert string to field.
 4666// If the string is invalid, do not modify field and return false.
 4667// In case of success, return true
 4668bool dmmeta::value_SetStrptrMaybe(dmmeta::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
 4669    bool ret = false;
 4670    switch (elems_N(rhs)) {
 4671        case 2: {
 4672            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE16(rhs.elems))) {
 4673                case LE_STR2('i','d'): {
 4674                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_id); ret = true; break;
 4675                }
 4676                case LE_STR2('n','s'): {
 4677                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_ns); ret = true; break;
 4678                }
 4679                case LE_STR2('o','p'): {
 4680                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_op); ret = true; break;
 4681                }
 4682                case LE_STR2('u','p'): {
 4683                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_up); ret = true; break;
 4684                }
 4685            }
 4686            break;
 4687        }
 4688        case 3: {
 4689            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE16(rhs.elems))|(u64(rhs[2])<<16)) {
 4690                case LE_STR3('a','r','g'): {
 4691                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_arg); ret = true; break;
 4692                }
 4693                case LE_STR3('d','e','l'): {
 4694                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_del); ret = true; break;
 4695                }
 4696                case LE_STR3('i','n','c'): {
 4697                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_inc); ret = true; break;
 4698                }
 4699                case LE_STR3('i','n','l'): {
 4700                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_inl); ret = true; break;
 4701                }
 4702                case LE_STR3('l','e','n'): {
 4703                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_len); ret = true; break;
 4704                }
 4705                case LE_STR3('m','a','x'): {
 4706                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_max); ret = true; break;
 4707                }
 4708                case LE_STR3('m','i','n'): {
 4709                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_min); ret = true; break;
 4710                }
 4711                case LE_STR3('p','a','d'): {
 4712                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_pad); ret = true; break;
 4713                }
 4714                case LE_STR3('p','o','s'): {
 4715                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_pos); ret = true; break;
 4716                }
 4717                case LE_STR3('r','e','t'): {
 4718                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_ret); ret = true; break;

 4720                case LE_STR3('s','e','p'): {
 4721                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_sep); ret = true; break;
 4722                }
 4723                case LE_STR3('s','e','t'): {
 4724                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_set); ret = true; break;
 4725                }
 4726                case LE_STR3('s','y','s'): {
 4727                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_sys); ret = true; break;
 4728                }
 4729                case LE_STR3('u','n','k'): {
 4730                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_unk); ret = true; break;
 4731                }
 4732                case LE_STR3('v','i','a'): {
 4733                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_via); ret = true; break;
 4734                }
 4735            }
 4736            break;
 4737        }
 4738        case 4: {
 4739            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))) {
 4740                case LE_STR4('b','a','s','e'): {
 4741                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_base); ret = true; break;
 4742                }
 4743                case LE_STR4('b','o','d','y'): {
 4744                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_body); ret = true; break;
 4745                }
 4746                case LE_STR4('c','a','l','c'): {
 4747                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_calc); ret = true; break;
 4748                }
 4749                case LE_STR4('c','a','l','l'): {
 4750                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_call); ret = true; break;
 4751                }
 4752                case LE_STR4('c','f','m','t'): {
 4753                    value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_cfmt); ret = true; break;
 4754                }

 5231                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ve",2)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_cumulative); ret = true; break; }
 5232                    break;
 5233                }
 5234                case LE_STR8('i','n','i','t','m','e','m','s'): {
 5235                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"et",2)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_initmemset); ret = true; break; }
 5236                    break;
 5237                }
 5238                case LE_STR8('r','i','g','h','t','F','i','e'): {
 5239                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ld",2)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_rightField); ret = true; break; }
 5240                    break;
 5241                }
 5242                case LE_STR8('s','y','m','b','o','l','t','y'): {
 5243                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"pe",2)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_symboltype); ret = true; break; }
 5244                    break;
 5245                }
 5246            }
 5247            break;
 5248        }
 5249        case 11: {
 5250            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
 5251                case LE_STR8('b','a','s','e','c','m','d','l'): {
 5252                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ine",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_basecmdline); ret = true; break; }
 5253                    break;
 5254                }
 5255                case LE_STR8('n','a','m','e','f','l','d','c'): {
 5256                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"typ",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_namefldctyp); ret = true; break; }
 5257                    break;
 5258                }
 5259                case LE_STR8('u','s','e','b','a','s','e','p'): {
 5260                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ool",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_usebasepool); ret = true; break; }
 5261                    break;
 5262                }
 5263                case LE_STR8('v','e','r','s','i','o','n','s'): {
 5264                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ort",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_versionsort); ret = true; break; }
 5265                    break;
 5266                }
 5267            }
 5268            break;
 5269        }
 5270        case 12: {
 5271            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
 5272                case LE_STR8('d','i','s','p','a','t','c','h'): {
 5273                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"_msg",4)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_dispatch_msg); ret = true; break; }
 5274                    break;
 5275                }
 5276                case LE_STR8('f','i','l','t','e','r','_','p'): {
 5277                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"rint",4)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_filter_print); ret = true; break; }
 5278                    break;
 5279                }
 5280                case LE_STR8('p','a','r','e','n','t','_','c'): {
 5281                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"type",4)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_parent_ctype); ret = true; break; }
 5282                    break;
 5283                }
 5284                case LE_STR8('p','a','r','e','n','t','_','f'): {
 5285                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ield",4)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_parent_field); ret = true; break; }
 5286                    break;
 5287                }
 5288                case LE_STR8('s','t','r','i','p','c','o','m'): {
 5289                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ment",4)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_stripcomment); ret = true; break; }
 5290                    break;
 5291                }
 5292            }
 5293            break;
 5294        }
 5295        case 14: {
 5296            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
 5297                case LE_STR8('c','h','i','l','d','_','s','s'): {
 5298                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"imfile",6)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_child_ssimfile); ret = true; break; }
 5299                    break;
 5300                }
 5301            }
 5302            break;
 5303        }
 5304        case 15: {
 5305            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
 5306                case LE_STR8('p','m','a','s','k','f','l','d'): {
 5307                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"_member",7)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_pmaskfld_member); ret = true; break; }
 5308                    break;
 5309                }
 5310            }
 5311            break;
 5312        }
 5313        case 19: {
 5314            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
 5315                case LE_STR8('c','o','r','r','e','c','t','_'): {
 5316                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"getorcreate",11)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_FieldId_correct_getorcreate); ret = true; break; }
 5317                    break;
 5318                }
 5319            }
 5320            break;
 5321        }
 5322    }
 5323    return ret;
 5324}
 5325
 5326// --- dmmeta.FieldId.value.SetStrptr
 5327// Convert string to field.
 5328// If the string is invalid, set numeric value to DFLT
 5329void dmmeta::value_SetStrptr(dmmeta::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs, dmmeta_FieldIdEnum dflt) {
 5330    if (!value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs)) value_SetEnum(parent,dflt);
 5331}
 5332
 5333// --- dmmeta.FieldId.value.ReadStrptrMaybe
 5334// Convert string to field. Return success value
 5335bool dmmeta::value_ReadStrptrMaybe(dmmeta::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
 5336    bool retval = false;
 5337    retval = value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs); // try symbol conversion
 5338    if (!retval) { // didn't work? try reading as underlying type
 5339        retval = i32_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.value,rhs);
 5340    }
 5341    return retval;
 5342}
 5343
 5344// --- dmmeta.FieldId..ReadStrptrMaybe
 5345// Read fields of dmmeta::FieldId from an ascii string.
 5346// The format of the string is the format of the dmmeta::FieldId's only field
 5347bool dmmeta::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(dmmeta::FieldId &parent, algo::strptr in_str) {
 5348    bool retval = true;
 5349    retval = retval && value_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent, in_str);
 5350    return retval;
 5351}

 5360// --- dmmeta.Findrem..ReadFieldMaybe
 5361bool dmmeta::Findrem_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Findrem& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
 5362    bool retval = true;
 5363    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
 5364    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
 5365    switch(field_id) {
 5366        case dmmeta_FieldId_field: {
 5367            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.field, strval);
 5368            break;
 5369        }
 5370        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
 5371            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
 5372            break;
 5373        }
 5374        default: break;
 5375    }
 5376    if (!retval) {
 5377        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 5378    }
 5379    return retval;
 5380}

 5388    ind_beg(algo::Attr_curs, attr, in_str) {
 5389        retval = retval && Findrem_ReadFieldMaybe(parent, attr.name, attr.value);
 5390    }ind_end;
 5391    return retval;
 5392}

 5420// --- dmmeta.Finput..ReadFieldMaybe
 5421bool dmmeta::Finput_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Finput& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
 5422    bool retval = true;
 5423    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
 5424    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
 5425    switch(field_id) {
 5426        case dmmeta_FieldId_field: {
 5427            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.field, strval);
 5428            break;
 5429        }
 5430        case dmmeta_FieldId_ns: {
 5431            retval = false;
 5432            break;
 5433        }
 5434        case dmmeta_FieldId_extrn: {
 5435            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.extrn, strval);
 5436            break;
 5437        }
 5438        case dmmeta_FieldId_update: {
 5439            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.update, strval);
 5440            break;
 5441        }
 5442        case dmmeta_FieldId_strict: {
 5443            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.strict, strval);
 5444            break;
 5445        }
 5446        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
 5447            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
 5448            break;
 5449        }
 5450        default: break;
 5451    }
 5452    if (!retval) {
 5453        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 5454    }
 5455    return retval;
 5456}

 5939    bool retval = true;

 5943        case dmmeta_FieldId_fstep: {

 5948            retval = false;
 5949            break;
 5950        }

 5952            retval = false;
 5953            break;
 5954        }
 5955        case dmmeta_FieldId_name: {
 5956            retval = false;
 5957            break;
 5958        }
 5959        case dmmeta_FieldId_steptype: {
 5960            retval = algo::Smallstr50_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.steptype, strval);
 5961            break;
 5962        }
 5963        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
 5964            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
 5965            break;
 5966        }
 5967        default: break;
 5968    }
 5969    if (!retval) {
 5970        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 5971    }
 5972    return retval;

 7620bool dmmeta::Nsinclude_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Nsinclude& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
 7621    bool retval = true;
 7622    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
 7623    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
 7624    switch(field_id) {
 7625        case dmmeta_FieldId_nsinclude: {
 7626            retval = algo::Smallstr50_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.nsinclude, strval);
 7627            break;
 7628        }
 7629        case dmmeta_FieldId_ns: {
 7630            retval = false;
 7631            break;
 7632        }
 7633        case dmmeta_FieldId_name: {
 7634            retval = false;
 7635            break;
 7636        }
 7637        case dmmeta_FieldId_sys: {
 7638            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.sys, strval);
 7639            break;
 7640        }
 7641        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
 7642            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
 7643            break;
 7644        }
 7645        default: break;
 7646    }
 7647    if (!retval) {
 7648        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 7649    }
 7650    return retval;
 7651}

 8024}

 8509    parent.isxref = bool(false);
 8510    parent.del = bool(false);
 8511    parent.up = bool(false);
 8512    parent.isnew = bool(false);
 8513    parent.hasalloc = bool(false);
 8514    parent.inst = bool(false);
 8515    parent.varlen = bool(false);
 8516}

 8561
 8562// --- dmmeta.ReftypeCase.reftype.ToCstr
 8563// Convert numeric value of field to one of predefined string constants.
 8564// If string is found, return a static C string. Otherwise, return NULL.
 8565const char* dmmeta::reftype_ToCstr(const dmmeta::ReftypeCase& parent) {
 8566    const char *ret = NULL;
 8567    switch(reftype_GetEnum(parent)) {
 8568        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Alias      : ret = "Alias";  break;
 8569        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Atree      : ret = "Atree";  break;
 8570        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Base       : ret = "Base";  break;
 8571        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Bheap      : ret = "Bheap";  break;
 8572        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Bitfld     : ret = "Bitfld";  break;
 8573        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Blkpool    : ret = "Blkpool";  break;
 8574        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Charset    : ret = "Charset";  break;
 8575        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Count      : ret = "Count";  break;
 8576        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Cppstack   : ret = "Cppstack";  break;
 8577        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Delptr     : ret = "Delptr";  break;
 8578        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Exec       : ret = "Exec";  break;
 8579        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Fbuf       : ret = "Fbuf";  break;
 8580        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Global     : ret = "Global";  break;
 8581        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Hook       : ret = "Hook";  break;
 8582        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Inlary     : ret = "Inlary";  break;
 8583        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Lary       : ret = "Lary";  break;
 8584        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Llist      : ret = "Llist";  break;
 8585        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Lpool      : ret = "Lpool";  break;
 8586        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Malloc     : ret = "Malloc";  break;
 8587        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Opt        : ret = "Opt";  break;
 8588        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Pkey       : ret = "Pkey";  break;
 8589        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Ptr        : ret = "Ptr";  break;
 8590        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Ptrary     : ret = "Ptrary";  break;
 8591        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Regx       : ret = "Regx";  break;
 8592        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_RegxSql    : ret = "RegxSql";  break;
 8593        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Sbrk       : ret = "Sbrk";  break;
 8594        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Smallstr   : ret = "Smallstr";  break;
 8595        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Tary       : ret = "Tary";  break;
 8596        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Thash      : ret = "Thash";  break;
 8597        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Tpool      : ret = "Tpool";  break;
 8598        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Upptr      : ret = "Upptr";  break;
 8599        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Val        : ret = "Val";  break;
 8600        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Varlen     : ret = "Varlen";  break;
 8601        case dmmeta_ReftypeCase_ZSListMT   : ret = "ZSListMT";  break;
 8602    }
 8603    return ret;
 8604}
 8605
 8606// --- dmmeta.ReftypeCase.reftype.Print
 8607// Convert reftype to a string. First, attempt conversion to a known string.
 8608// If no string matches, print reftype as a numeric value.
 8609void dmmeta::reftype_Print(const dmmeta::ReftypeCase& parent, algo::cstring &lhs) {
 8610    const char *strval = reftype_ToCstr(parent);
 8611    if (strval) {
 8612        lhs << strval;
 8613    } else {
 8614        lhs << parent.reftype;
 8615    }
 8616}
 8617
 8618// --- dmmeta.ReftypeCase.reftype.SetStrptrMaybe
 8619// Convert string to field.
 8620// If the string is invalid, do not modify field and return false.
 8621// In case of success, return true
 8622bool dmmeta::reftype_SetStrptrMaybe(dmmeta::ReftypeCase& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
 8623    bool ret = false;
 8624    switch (elems_N(rhs)) {
 8625        case 3: {
 8626            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE16(rhs.elems))|(u64(rhs[2])<<16)) {
 8627                case LE_STR3('O','p','t'): {
 8628                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Opt); ret = true; break;
 8629                }
 8630                case LE_STR3('P','t','r'): {
 8631                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Ptr); ret = true; break;
 8632                }
 8633                case LE_STR3('V','a','l'): {
 8634                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Val); ret = true; break;
 8635                }
 8636            }
 8637            break;
 8638        }
 8639        case 4: {
 8640            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))) {
 8641                case LE_STR4('B','a','s','e'): {
 8642                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Base); ret = true; break;
 8643                }
 8644                case LE_STR4('E','x','e','c'): {
 8645                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Exec); ret = true; break;
 8646                }
 8647                case LE_STR4('F','b','u','f'): {
 8648                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Fbuf); ret = true; break;
 8649                }
 8650                case LE_STR4('H','o','o','k'): {
 8651                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Hook); ret = true; break;
 8652                }
 8653                case LE_STR4('L','a','r','y'): {
 8654                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Lary); ret = true; break;
 8655                }
 8656                case LE_STR4('P','k','e','y'): {
 8657                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Pkey); ret = true; break;
 8658                }
 8659                case LE_STR4('R','e','g','x'): {
 8660                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Regx); ret = true; break;
 8661                }
 8662                case LE_STR4('S','b','r','k'): {
 8663                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Sbrk); ret = true; break;
 8664                }
 8665                case LE_STR4('T','a','r','y'): {
 8666                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Tary); ret = true; break;
 8667                }
 8668            }
 8669            break;
 8670        }
 8671        case 5: {
 8672            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(rhs[4])<<32)) {
 8673                case LE_STR5('A','l','i','a','s'): {
 8674                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Alias); ret = true; break;
 8675                }
 8676                case LE_STR5('A','t','r','e','e'): {
 8677                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Atree); ret = true; break;
 8678                }
 8679                case LE_STR5('B','h','e','a','p'): {
 8680                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Bheap); ret = true; break;
 8681                }
 8682                case LE_STR5('C','o','u','n','t'): {
 8683                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Count); ret = true; break;
 8684                }
 8685                case LE_STR5('L','l','i','s','t'): {
 8686                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Llist); ret = true; break;
 8687                }
 8688                case LE_STR5('L','p','o','o','l'): {
 8689                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Lpool); ret = true; break;
 8690                }
 8691                case LE_STR5('T','h','a','s','h'): {
 8692                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Thash); ret = true; break;
 8693                }
 8694                case LE_STR5('T','p','o','o','l'): {
 8695                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Tpool); ret = true; break;
 8696                }
 8697                case LE_STR5('U','p','p','t','r'): {
 8698                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Upptr); ret = true; break;
 8699                }
 8700            }
 8701            break;
 8702        }
 8703        case 6: {
 8704            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(algo::ReadLE16(rhs.elems+4))<<32)) {
 8705                case LE_STR6('B','i','t','f','l','d'): {
 8706                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Bitfld); ret = true; break;
 8707                }
 8708                case LE_STR6('D','e','l','p','t','r'): {
 8709                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Delptr); ret = true; break;
 8710                }
 8711                case LE_STR6('G','l','o','b','a','l'): {
 8712                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Global); ret = true; break;
 8713                }
 8714                case LE_STR6('I','n','l','a','r','y'): {
 8715                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Inlary); ret = true; break;
 8716                }
 8717                case LE_STR6('M','a','l','l','o','c'): {
 8718                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Malloc); ret = true; break;
 8719                }
 8720                case LE_STR6('P','t','r','a','r','y'): {
 8721                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Ptrary); ret = true; break;
 8722                }
 8723                case LE_STR6('V','a','r','l','e','n'): {
 8724                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Varlen); ret = true; break;
 8725                }
 8726            }
 8727            break;
 8728        }
 8729        case 7: {
 8730            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(algo::ReadLE16(rhs.elems+4))<<32)|(u64(rhs[6])<<48)) {
 8731                case LE_STR7('B','l','k','p','o','o','l'): {
 8732                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Blkpool); ret = true; break;
 8733                }
 8734                case LE_STR7('C','h','a','r','s','e','t'): {
 8735                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Charset); ret = true; break;
 8736                }
 8737                case LE_STR7('R','e','g','x','S','q','l'): {
 8738                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_RegxSql); ret = true; break;
 8739                }
 8740            }
 8741            break;
 8742        }
 8743        case 8: {
 8744            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
 8745                case LE_STR8('C','p','p','s','t','a','c','k'): {
 8746                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Cppstack); ret = true; break;
 8747                }
 8748                case LE_STR8('S','m','a','l','l','s','t','r'): {
 8749                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_Smallstr); ret = true; break;
 8750                }
 8751                case LE_STR8('Z','S','L','i','s','t','M','T'): {
 8752                    reftype_SetEnum(parent,dmmeta_ReftypeCase_ZSListMT); ret = true; break;
 8753                }
 8754            }
 8755            break;
 8756        }
 8757    }
 8758    return ret;
 8759}
 8760
 8761// --- dmmeta.ReftypeCase.reftype.SetStrptr
 8762// Convert string to field.
 8763// If the string is invalid, set numeric value to DFLT
 8764void dmmeta::reftype_SetStrptr(dmmeta::ReftypeCase& parent, algo::strptr rhs, dmmeta_ReftypeCaseEnum dflt) {
 8765    if (!reftype_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs)) reftype_SetEnum(parent,dflt);
 8766}

 8768// --- dmmeta.Rowid..ReadFieldMaybe
 8769bool dmmeta::Rowid_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Rowid& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
 8770    bool retval = true;
 8771    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
 8772    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
 8773    switch(field_id) {
 8774        case dmmeta_FieldId_field: {
 8775            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.field, strval);
 8776            break;
 8777        }
 8778        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
 8779            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
 8780            break;
 8781        }
 8782        default: break;
 8783    }
 8784    if (!retval) {
 8785        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 8786    }
 8787    return retval;
 8788}
 8789
 8790// --- dmmeta.Rowid..ReadStrptrMaybe
 8791// Read fields of dmmeta::Rowid from an ascii string.
 8792// The format of the string is an ssim Tuple
 8793bool dmmeta::Rowid_ReadStrptrMaybe(dmmeta::Rowid &parent, algo::strptr in_str) {
 8794    bool retval = true;
 8795    retval = algo::StripTypeTag(in_str, "dmmeta.rowid") || algo::StripTypeTag(in_str, "dmmeta.Rowid");
 8796    ind_beg(algo::Attr_curs, attr, in_str) {
 8797        retval = retval && Rowid_ReadFieldMaybe(parent, attr.name, attr.value);
 8798    }ind_end;
 8799    return retval;
 8800}

 8803// print string representation of ROW to string STR
 8804// cfmt:dmmeta.Rowid.String  printfmt:Tuple
 8805void dmmeta::Rowid_Print(dmmeta::Rowid& row, algo::cstring& str) {

 8809    algo::Smallstr100_Print(row.field, temp);
 8810    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"field", temp);
 8811
 8812    algo::Comment_Print(row.comment, temp);
 8813    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"comment", temp);
 8814}

 8828// --- dmmeta.Smallstr..ReadFieldMaybe
 8829bool dmmeta::Smallstr_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Smallstr& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
 8830    bool retval = true;
 8831    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
 8832    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
 8833    switch(field_id) {
 8834        case dmmeta_FieldId_field: {
 8835            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.field, strval);
 8836            break;
 8837        }
 8838        case dmmeta_FieldId_ctype: {
 8839            retval = false;
 8840            break;
 8841        }
 8842        case dmmeta_FieldId_length: {
 8843            retval = i32_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.length, strval);
 8844            break;
 8845        }
 8846        case dmmeta_FieldId_strtype: {
 8847            retval = algo::Smallstr50_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.strtype, strval);
 8848            break;
 8849        }
 8850        case dmmeta_FieldId_pad: {
 8851            retval = algo::CppExpr_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.pad, strval);
 8852            break;
 8853        }
 8854        case dmmeta_FieldId_strict: {
 8855            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.strict, strval);
 8856            break;
 8857        }
 8858        default: break;
 8859    }
 8860    if (!retval) {
 8861        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 8862    }
 8863    return retval;
 8864}

 8872    ind_beg(algo::Attr_curs, attr, in_str) {
 8873        retval = retval && Smallstr_ReadFieldMaybe(parent, attr.name, attr.value);
 8874    }ind_end;
 8875    return retval;

 8878// --- dmmeta.Smallstr..Print
 8879// print string representation of ROW to string STR
 8880// cfmt:dmmeta.Smallstr.String  printfmt:Tuple
 8881void dmmeta::Smallstr_Print(dmmeta::Smallstr& row, algo::cstring& str) {

 8892    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"strtype", temp);

 8895    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"pad", temp);
 8896
 8897    bool_Print(row.strict, temp);
 8898    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"strict", temp);
 8899}

 9088// --- dmmeta.Ssimfile..ReadFieldMaybe
 9089bool dmmeta::Ssimfile_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Ssimfile& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
 9090    bool retval = true;
 9091    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
 9092    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
 9093    switch(field_id) {
 9094        case dmmeta_FieldId_ssimfile: {
 9095            retval = algo::Smallstr50_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.ssimfile, strval);
 9096            break;
 9097        }
 9098        case dmmeta_FieldId_ssimns: {
 9099            retval = false;
 9100            break;
 9101        }
 9102        case dmmeta_FieldId_ns: {
 9103            retval = false;
 9104            break;
 9105        }
 9106        case dmmeta_FieldId_name: {
 9107            retval = false;
 9108            break;
 9109        }
 9110        case dmmeta_FieldId_ctype: {
 9111            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.ctype, strval);
 9112            break;
 9113        }
 9114        default: break;
 9115    }
 9116    if (!retval) {
 9117        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 9118    }
 9119    return retval;
 9120}

 9213// --- dmmeta.Ssimreq..ReadFieldMaybe
 9214bool dmmeta::Ssimreq_ReadFieldMaybe(dmmeta::Ssimreq& parent, algo::strptr field, algo::strptr strval) {
 9215    bool retval = true;
 9216    dmmeta::FieldId field_id;
 9217    (void)value_SetStrptrMaybe(field_id,field);
 9218    switch(field_id) {
 9219        case dmmeta_FieldId_ssimreq: {
 9220            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.ssimreq, strval);
 9221            break;
 9222        }
 9223        case dmmeta_FieldId_parent: {
 9224            retval = algo::Smallstr100_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.parent, strval);
 9225            break;
 9226        }
 9227        case dmmeta_FieldId_parent_field: {
 9228            retval = false;
 9229            break;
 9230        }
 9231        case dmmeta_FieldId_parent_ctype: {
 9232            retval = false;
 9233            break;
 9234        }
 9235        case dmmeta_FieldId_value: {
 9236            retval = false;
 9237            break;
 9238        }
 9239        case dmmeta_FieldId_child_ssimfile: {
 9240            retval = false;
 9241            break;
 9242        }
 9243        case dmmeta_FieldId_child_key: {
 9244            retval = false;
 9245            break;
 9246        }
 9247        case dmmeta_FieldId_reqchild: {
 9248            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.reqchild, strval);
 9249            break;
 9250        }
 9251        case dmmeta_FieldId_bidir: {
 9252            retval = bool_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.bidir, strval);
 9253            break;
 9254        }
 9255        case dmmeta_FieldId_comment: {
 9256            retval = algo::Comment_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.comment, strval);
 9257            break;
 9258        }
 9259        default: break;
 9260    }
 9261    if (!retval) {
 9262        algo_lib::AppendErrtext("attr",field);
 9263    }
 9264    return retval;
 9265}

 9304
 9305    algo::Comment_Print(row.comment, temp);
 9306    PrintAttrSpaceReset(str,"comment", temp);
